1
00:00:02,067 --> 00:00:06,400
(One year ago)
The final member to join Wakers is...

2
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:09,400
Congratulations to trainee Kim Hyunjae.

3
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:12,900
Idol Audition Show "Next Stage"

4
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:16,467
Hyunjae, congrats!

5
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,967
Thanks.

6
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:20,267
I'm definitely going to debut, so...

7
00:00:20,367 --> 00:00:22,067
Let's see each other again for sure.

8
00:00:22,167 --> 00:00:23,900
Okay.

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,633
We have to meet again.

10
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:29,167
So, I'll be in touch...

11
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:32,967
We can keep in touch, right?

12
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,933
Yeah, of course.

13
00:00:37,033 --> 00:00:40,467
Let's give him another
big round of applause.

14
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:50,300
Now, let's hear from trainee Kim Hyunjae.

15
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,800
Hyunjae! What are you
doing here all of a sudden?

16
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:03,767
I skipped practice.

17
00:01:04,533 --> 00:01:05,613
Are you allowed to do that?

18
00:01:05,700 --> 00:01:08,500
Promotions will start tomorrow,
so we might get busier.

19
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:12,033
That's why I wanted to see you first.

20
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:17,500
Well, you've seen me now.

21
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,033
Is there anything else?

22
00:01:24,033 --> 00:01:25,467
No, that's all.

23
00:01:25,567 --> 00:01:27,767
You should go back before
your company finds out.

24
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:35,267
Hyunjae.

25
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,267
Do well on your promotions.

26
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,467
Hwaiting!

27
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:15,767
That was insane. I almost fell for you.

28
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,100
Oh, come on.

29
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,800
They really don't give us a break.

30
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:22,567
Looks like they're planning to
run us into the ground this year.

31
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:24,833
It's brutal.

32
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:26,509
You're not feeling sick
or anything, are you?

33
00:02:26,533 --> 00:02:27,433
Of course not.

34
00:02:27,533 --> 00:02:29,233
How about you? How have things been?

35
00:02:29,333 --> 00:02:33,233
I've been getting more fans lately,
and the company is really promoting me.

36
00:02:33,333 --> 00:02:34,833
Maybe I'll get to debut soon?

37
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:38,013
We'll be seeing each other on stage
soon, so watch out. You'd better be ready.

38
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:41,000
Yes, sir. I'll be waiting.

39
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,567
(Finally done.)

40
00:02:57,933 --> 00:02:58,933
(What are you up to?)

41
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,367
Finally done...

42
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:01,833
You're done?

43
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:03,100
Yeah.

44
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:06,000
Did I wake you at this hour?

45
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:08,800
No, I was just practicing.

46
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,867
And waiting for you to text back.

47
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:15,900
You were practicing? You must be tired...

48
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,733
Not at all, it must be harder for you.

49
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:19,467
You're the one who's working harder.

50
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:22,133
You must be exhausted. Go get some sleep.

51
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:24,133
You get some sleep too.

52
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:36,000
(Have you eaten?)

53
00:03:40,733 --> 00:03:43,833
Hey! Should I audition for a girl group?

54
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,267
Who are you texting right now?

55
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,120
(Want to grab a bite? I haven't eaten yet.)

56
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:56,333
What are you waiting for? Just send it.

57
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:57,967
Forget it, I'll send it.

58
00:03:58,067 --> 00:03:59,500
Hey, give it back.

59
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:12,067
(I miss you, Hyunjae. Don't you miss me?)

60
00:04:21,133 --> 00:04:23,433
Sooan, are you practicing?

61
00:04:23,533 --> 00:04:25,067
I'm sorry...

62
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:27,433
The debut plan we talked about...

63
00:04:27,533 --> 00:04:29,013
I'm afraid it's been postponed again.

64
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,033
The company isn't
doing so well right now...

65
00:04:31,133 --> 00:04:34,367
The CEO is looking for new investors, so...

66
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:35,767
Just wait a little longer.

67
00:04:35,867 --> 00:04:37,233
Okay.

68
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:38,600
I understand.

69
00:04:39,533 --> 00:04:40,967
Also, starting tomorrow...

70
00:04:41,067 --> 00:04:43,600
we're putting practice
on hold for a while.

71
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:44,700
What?

72
00:04:44,767 --> 00:04:47,633
We couldn't renew the
lease on the practice room.

73
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:50,433
I'll let you know when we find a new place.

74
00:04:50,867 --> 00:04:52,167
Okay.

75
00:05:07,267 --> 00:05:09,800
Welcome! Hello, everyone! We are Wakers!

76
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,709
(A thoughtful star) / (Happy birthday
to you~ x2) Happy birthday to you~

77
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:12,813
(The guys keep teasing me.)

78
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:15,113
Let's get some of the
birthday boy's good luck!

79
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:23,233
(I miss you, Hyunjae. Don't you miss me?)

80
00:05:29,533 --> 00:05:32,333
(You must be busy lately. I'm also bus...)

81
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:36,500
Hyunjae, congratulations.

82
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:39,867
I'll debut too. We'll
definitely see each other again.

83
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:42,300
I'm sorry, the company
isn't doing so well right now.

84
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:45,067
We couldn't renew the
lease on the practice room.

85
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:47,767
(Block Contact)
I'll let you know when there's news.

86
00:05:48,367 --> 00:05:50,467
"Love Class" Season 3
(Episode 3)

87
00:05:58,867 --> 00:06:00,600
(Incoming Call: Mom)

88
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:06,267
Mom, I did everything you told me to.

89
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:08,667
I'm working hard, so don't worry.

90
00:06:09,767 --> 00:06:13,167
Yeah... I'll do that.

91
00:06:14,933 --> 00:06:16,667
Okay, I'm hanging up.

92
00:06:24,933 --> 00:06:26,567
It's gotten cold.

93
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:36,000
Are you a zombie?

94
00:06:36,733 --> 00:06:38,433
You're done practicing?

95
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,000
It's so cold.

96
00:06:43,633 --> 00:06:44,800
Drink it anyway.

97
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:46,860
Haven't you been saying
you can't wake up lately?

98
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:51,600
Coffee is meant to be drunk hot.

99
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:53,533
Then, should I "warm it up" for you?

100
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,067
Hey, wait, someone could walk in.

101
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:12,933
No one's coming! It's fine.

102
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,133
Ah... I smell like sweat.

103
00:07:15,233 --> 00:07:16,833
No, you don't.

104
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:19,367
Just for a second...

105
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,833
Let me hold you.

106
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,633
Is it a little warmer now?

107
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:47,000
(LUXE Hotel)
This doesn't feel right...

108
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,767
Pay off your debt.

109
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:56,367
With your body.

110
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:02,133
What on earth is he thinking?

111
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:09,400
This is awkward. I'm going in first.

112
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:16,967
What's wrong?

113
00:08:17,067 --> 00:08:18,967
You're the one who wanted to come here.

114
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:24,576
Don't judge it by its cover.

115
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,433
It's probably nice inside.

116
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,533
Everyone's looking at us strangely.

117
00:08:29,633 --> 00:08:31,133
Hurry up.

118
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,700
Ah...

119
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,033
What the heck?

120
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:43,500
You already booked a room?

121
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,867
I didn't realize you were in such a hurry.

122
00:08:49,567 --> 00:08:51,567
Ah... Is this right?

123
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:54,500
Hey, wait for me.

124
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:19,433
What was I thinking?

125
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:22,667
Why did you suddenly show up?

126
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,160
If there's nothing else, I'll be going.

127
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:32,767
This... You didn't leave this for
me to see on purpose, did you?

128
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,000
Why did you ghost me?

129
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,967
Ghost you?

130
00:09:55,567 --> 00:09:57,100
Never mind...

131
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:02,343
We're not in the type of relationship
that always keeps in touch anyway.

132
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:03,600
Then what are we?

133
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:05,767
A business relationship.

134
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:07,409
We were just using each other, weren't we?

135
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,867
You got to debut. Isn't that enough?

136
00:10:09,967 --> 00:10:10,967
What?

137
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:13,033
It was all an act.

138
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,400
What else could it have been?

139
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:21,400
You really don't have any feelings for me?

140
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,367
In Korea...

141
00:11:17,467 --> 00:11:19,600
there's one thing you
have to do after moving.

142
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:34,000
Cheers!

143
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,500
What's wrong?

144
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:48,133
Nothing, I just didn't expect
you to be such a good drinker.

145
00:11:48,933 --> 00:11:51,000
Didn't you say that in Korea...

146
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,400
you have to down
the first shot in one go?

147
00:11:55,067 --> 00:11:57,600
What genius taught you that?

148
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,033
This is so good.

149
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:17,667
Why are you drinking so fast?

150
00:12:17,767 --> 00:12:19,433
Can you really hold your liquor?

151
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,533
I don't know.

152
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,267
You don't usually drink?

153
00:12:24,367 --> 00:12:26,600
Is it because you're
from a Buddhist country?

154
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:29,267
No... I'm a damn good drinker.

155
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:30,833
Wow.

156
00:12:30,933 --> 00:12:32,443
Why is that the kind of thing you pick up?

157
00:12:32,467 --> 00:12:34,767
My pronunciation was damn perfect, right?

158
00:12:34,867 --> 00:12:36,933
Yeah, it was damn perfect.

159
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:40,000
But that word is considered
a bad word in Korea.

160
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,767
But you speak informally to me.

161
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:47,167
You're actually Korean, aren't you?

162
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:52,267
Hey... it's bad luck to
pour your own drink.

163
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:02,533
Your glass isn't even empty...

164
00:13:22,333 --> 00:13:24,600
You really don't have feelings for me?

165
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:52,733
I was worried I might have
some lingering feelings...

166
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,667
but I'm glad I don't.

167
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:02,767
"Love Class" Season 3

168
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:06,033
(Episode 4 Preview)

169
00:14:06,133 --> 00:14:08,867
Why can't I remember anything, for real?!

170
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,333
Did you sleep well?

171
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,467
Um...

172
00:14:11,567 --> 00:14:13,567
I didn't say anything weird, did I?

173
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:15,200
I don't know.

174
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,567
I can't speak Korean.

175
00:14:16,667 --> 00:14:18,600
Wasn't it enough to use me for clout?

176
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:20,800
Is there anything else you want from me?

177
00:14:22,133 --> 00:14:23,543
What, do you want me to sleep with you?

178
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:25,500
Don't ever show up in front of me again.

179
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:30,133
Fine, if that's what you really want.

